---
import imgAgbaje from '~/assets/images/waist-to-height-calculator/professor-agbaje-waist-to-height-ratio-calculator-demonstration.webp';
import imgCalculator from '~/assets/images/waist-to-height-calculator/waist-to-height-ratio-calculator-with-a-measurement-tape.webp';
import imgBMI from '~/assets/images/waist-to-height-calculator/waist-to-height-ratio-category-whtr-vs-bmi-category.webp';
import Calculator from '~/components/ui/calculator/Calculator.astro';
import GradientText from '~/components/ui/GradientText.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import ContentSection from '~/components/widgets/ContentSection.astro';
import Features4 from '~/components/widgets/Features4.astro';
import GraphGrid from '~/components/widgets/GraphGrid.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Note from '~/components/widgets/Note.astro';
import { references } from '~/data/calculatorReferences';
import { THRESHOLDS } from '~/data/thresholds';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { YouTube } from 'astro-embed';

const metadata = {
  title: 'New Waist to Height Ratio Calculator – Measure at Home',
  description:
    'Waist to height ratio calculator with visual and color-coded results. Based on the largest WHtR dataset to assess body fat and find your healthy range.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: true,
  openGraph: {
    title: 'New Waist to Height Ratio Calculator – Measure at Home',
    description:
      'Waist to height ratio calculator with visual and color-coded results. Based on the largest WHtR dataset to assess body fat and find your healthy range.',
    type: 'website',
    image: imgCalculator,
    article: {
      publishedTime: '2025-01-17T05:05:14+02:00',
      modifiedTime: '2025-01-17T05:05:14+02:00',
      authors: ['urFIT-child Research Group'],
      tags: [
        'waist to height ratio calculator',
        'waist height ratio calculator',
        'waist to height calculator',
        'ideal waist size calculator',
        'waist size calculator',
        'height to waist calculator',
        'WHtR',
        'central obesity calculator',
        'Dr. Andrew Agbaje',
        'urFIT calculator',
      ],
    },
  },
  twitter: {
    handle: '@urFIT-child',
    site: '@urFIT-child',
    cardType: 'summary_large_image',
  },
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata} schemaType="calculator">
  <Content
    id="waist-to-height-1"
    tagline="Waist/Height calculator"
    title="New Waist to Height Ratio Calculator"
    subtitle="Waist to height ratio calculator is a simple, low-cost way to assess body fat mass and health risk. It offers a more accurate picture than BMI, and helps detect excess fat without the need for expensive tools."
    classes={{
      container: 'lg:pb-0 md:pb-0',
    }}
    image={{
      src: imgAgbaje,
      alt: 'Professor Andrew Agbaje, a leading childhood obesity researcher, demonstrating how to use a waist to height ratio calculator (WHtR) with a measuring tape.',
    }}
    imageText="Prof. Andrew Agbaje shows how to use a waist to height ratio calculator — a tool reshaping childhood health assessments beyond BMI."
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <div
        class="intersect-once intersect-tenth sm:intersect-quarter intercept-no-queue motion-safe:opacity-0 motion-safe:intersect:animate-fade"
      >
        <h3
          class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl xl:text-[30px] xl:leading-[36px] mb-2 xl:mb-[8px] font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white"
        >
          Waist circumference
        </h3>
        Acquire a flexible measuring tape or tape rule. Feel for your hip bone and your bottom rib, and place the tape measure
        evenly around your waist which is halfway between the last rib and hip bone. The waistline may lie directly above
        your umbilicus. (If needed, use a mirror to guide the tape straight around your waist and parallel to the ground.)
        Record the values in centimeters.
        <br />
        <br />

        <h3
          class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl xl:text-[30px] xl:leading-[36px] mb-2 xl:mb-[8px] font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white"
        >
          Height measurement
        </h3>
        A tape measure, a flat surface, and a pencil are needed. Stand with your feet without shoes flat on the floor with
        your heels against the corner where the wall and floor meet. Ensure your head, shoulders, and buttocks touch the
        wall. Look straight ahead parallel to the floor. Have someone place a book or a ruler over your head and lightly
        mark the wall with a pencil. Then measure the distance between the marked point and the floor. Now calculate waist
        circumference (cm)/height (cm) and check the results against the categories provided below.
      </div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Note
    text="Please do not diagnose overweight and obesity in children and adolescents with body mass index (BMI) alone. BMI was NEVER designed to detect obesity in an individual. Kindly use the waist to height ratio calculator to confirm if the body size is due to fat mass or if the children are simply heavy due to muscle mass."
    author="Prof. Andrew Agbaje"
    classes={{
      text: 'not-italic text-xl xl:text-[20px] xl:leading-[28px] max-w-4xl xl:max-w-[896px] mx-auto',
    }}
  />

  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->

  <Hero
    id="calculator"
    tagline="Calculate"
    title="Waist to height ratio calculator"
    classes={{
      titleClass: 'lg:text-[44px] lg:leading-[52px] xl:text-[44px] xl:leading-[52px]',
      labelContainerClass: 'lg:py-0 md:py-0 xl:py-0',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="image">
      <Calculator />
      <span class="text-base xl:text-[16px] xl:leading-[24px] block mt-8 xl:mt-[32px] text-center dark:text-slate-400"
        >1 inch = 2.54 cm</span
      >
    </Fragment>
  </Hero>

  <Content
    classes={{
      titleClass: 'lg:text-[44px] lg:leading-[52px] xl:text-[44px] xl:leading-[52px]',
      container: 'lg:pt-0 md:pt-0 xl:pt-0',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3
        class="text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white tracking-tight sm:text-2xl xl:text-[24px] xl:leading-[32px] mb-2 xl:mb-[8px]"
      >
        🎥 Video Tutorial:
        <br />
        How to Use the Waist to Height Ratio Calculator
      </h3>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl xl:text-[20px] xl:leading-[28px]">
        <!-- <GradientText class="font-semibold text-primary" style2
          >BBC Point West: how to calculate whtr with waist to height ratio calculator</GradientText
        > -->
        <br />
        <span class="text-black dark:text-white text-lg xl:text-[18px] xl:leading-[28px]">
          Learn how to measure waist to height ratio using our easy-to-use waist to height ratio calculator. Unlike
          regular tools, it gives visual and color-coded results to clearly show health risk levels. Backed by
          world-class research results and perfect for both children and adults, it's a smarter alternative to BMI.
        </span>
      </p>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="image">
      <div class="relative">
        <YouTube id="AuFbnDornog" title="How to measure waist to height ratio at home" params="start=101" />
      </div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Features2 Widget ************** -->

  <GraphGrid
    title="Result interpretation"
    columns={1}
    classes={{
      container: 'lg:pb-0 md:pb-0 xl:pb-0',
    }}
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Age Group',
        rows: [
          { text1: 'Childhood', text2: '' },
          { text1: 'Adolescence', text2: '' },
          { text1: 'Young Adulthood', text2: '' },
        ],
      },
      {
        title: 'Low fat',
        icon: { text: 'tabler:arrow-down-circle', class: 'text-purple-500' },
        colorClass: 'bg-purple-500',
        subtitle: { text1: 'Male', text2: 'Female' },
        rows: [
          { text1: `<${THRESHOLDS.male.low.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `<${THRESHOLDS.female.low.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `<${THRESHOLDS.male.low.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `<${THRESHOLDS.female.low.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `<${THRESHOLDS.male.low.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `<${THRESHOLDS.female.low.toFixed(2)}` },
        ],
      },
      {
        title: 'Normal fat',
        icon: { text: 'tabler:circle-check', class: 'text-green-500' },
        colorClass: 'bg-green-500',
        subtitle: { text1: 'Male', text2: 'Female' },
        rows: [
          { text1: `<${THRESHOLDS.male.normal.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `<${THRESHOLDS.female.normal.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `<${THRESHOLDS.male.normal.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `<${THRESHOLDS.female.normal.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `<${THRESHOLDS.male.normal.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `<${THRESHOLDS.female.normal.toFixed(2)}` },
        ],
      },
      {
        title: 'High fat',
        icon: { text: 'tabler:alert-triangle', class: 'text-yellow-500' },
        colorClass: 'bg-yellow-500',
        subtitle: { text1: 'Male', text2: 'Female' },
        rows: [
          { text1: `≥${THRESHOLDS.male.high.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `≥${THRESHOLDS.female.high.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `≥${THRESHOLDS.male.high.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `≥${THRESHOLDS.female.high.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `≥${THRESHOLDS.male.high.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `≥${THRESHOLDS.female.high.toFixed(2)}` },
        ],
      },
      {
        title: 'Excess fat',
        icon: { text: 'tabler:alert-octagon', class: 'text-red-500' },
        colorClass: 'bg-red-500',
        subtitle: { text1: 'Male', text2: 'Female' },
        rows: [
          { text1: `≥${THRESHOLDS.male.excess.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `≥${THRESHOLDS.female.excess.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `≥${THRESHOLDS.male.excess.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `≥${THRESHOLDS.female.excess.toFixed(2)}` },
          { text1: `≥${THRESHOLDS.male.excess.toFixed(2)}`, text2: `≥${THRESHOLDS.female.excess.toFixed(2)}` },
        ],
      },
    ]}
  />

  <ContentSection>
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <p
        class="text-base xl:text-[16px] xl:leading-[24px] intersect-once intersect-tenth sm:intersect-quarter intercept-no-queue motion-safe:opacity-0 motion-safe:intersect:animate-fade"
      >
        Obesity is a chronic relapsing disease of <GradientText class="font-bold">excess fat</GradientText> accumulation
        (adiposopathy) but not <GradientText class="font-bold">excess weight</GradientText>. To limit the stigma
        associated with obesity, we propose a new nomenclature of overweight as <GradientText class="font-bold"
          >adiposopathy grade 1</GradientText
        >
        (high fat) and obesity as <GradientText class="font-bold">adiposopathy grade 2</GradientText> (excess fat).
      </p>
    </Fragment>
  </ContentSection>

  <!-- HeroText Widget ******************* -->

  <ContentSection>
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <h3
        class="text-center text-2xl sm:text-3xl xl:text-[30px] xl:leading-[36px] mb-2 xl:mb-[8px] font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white intersect-once intersect-tenth sm:intersect-quarter intercept-no-queue motion-safe:opacity-0 motion-safe:intersect:animate-fade"
      >
        Benefits of using waist to height ratio calculator over body mass index (BMI)
      </h3>
      <br />
      <p
        class="text-base xl:text-[16px] xl:leading-[24px] intersect-once intersect-tenth sm:intersect-quarter intercept-no-queue motion-safe:opacity-0 motion-safe:intersect:animate-fade"
      >
        <!-- Waist circumference-to-height ratio had a very high agreement of 81 – 89% with DEXA-measured total body fat mass -->
        Waist to height ratio (WHtR) had a very high agreement of 81 – 89% with DEXA-measured total body fat mass and trunk
        fat mass, but a low agreement with muscle mass (24 – 39%). BMI had a moderate agreement with total fat mass and trunk
        fat mass (65 – 72%) and muscle mass (52 – 58%). Since BMI had a moderate agreement with DEXA-measured muscle mass,
        it is difficult to specify whether BMI measures excess fat or muscle mass.
        <GradientText class="font-bold inline">
          The optimal waist to height ratio cut points that predicted the 95th percentile of total fat mass in males was
          0.53 and 0.54 in females.
        </GradientText>
        This cut point detected 8 out of 10 males and 7 out of 10 females who truly had excess DEXA-measured fat. The cut
        point also identified 93 out of 100 males and 95 out of 100 females who truly do not have excess fat.
      </p>

      <Hero
        image={{
          src: imgCalculator,
          alt: 'Measuring tape wrapped around a waist to demonstrate how to use the waist to height ratio calculator (WHtR)',
          isInfographics: true,
        }}
        imageText="Measuring tape wrapped around a waist to demonstrate how to use the waist to height ratio calculator (WHtR)"
      />
      <p
        class="text-base xl:text-[16px] xl:leading-[24px] intersect-once intersect-tenth sm:intersect-quarter intercept-no-queue motion-safe:opacity-0 motion-safe:intersect:animate-fade"
      >
        “This study provides novel information that would be useful in updating future childhood obesity guidelines and
        policy statements. The average waist to height ratio in childhood, adolescence, and young adulthood is 0.45, it
        does not vary with age and among individuals like BMI. Waist to height ratio might be preferable to BMI
        assessment in children and adolescent clinics as an inexpensive tool for detecting excess body fat or abdominal
        fat. Parents should not be discouraged by the BMI or weight of their children but can inexpensively confirm
        whether the weight is due to increase in excess fat by examining their kid’s waist to height ratio.”
        <GradientText class="font-bold"> says Andrew Agbaje </GradientText>
      </p>

      <Hero
        image={{
          src: imgBMI,
          alt: 'Visual comparison of waist to height ratio (WHtR) categories vs BMI categories for assessing body fat.',
          height: 1333,
          width: 2000,
        }}
        imageText="Visual comparison of waist to height ratio (WHtR) categories vs BMI categories for assessing body fat."
      />
    </Fragment>
  </ContentSection>

  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->

  <Features4
    title="References"
    columns={3}
    classes={{
      container: 'max-w-5xl xl:max-w-[1024px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 xl:px-[24px] py-8 xl:py-[32px]',
      items: {
        container: 'gap-6 xl:gap-[24px]',
        itemContainer: 'items-start',
        text: 'text-start',
        title: 'text-xl xl:text-[20px] xl:leading-[28px]',
        subtitle: 'text-primary',
      },
    }}
    items={references}
  />
</Layout>
